# .trivyignore — Documented exceptions for CVEs that remain after --ignore-unfixed.
#
# Scan policy (enforced in both pr.yml and deploy.yml):
#   --ignore-unfixed   Trivy filters CVEs where no patched package version exists
#                      in the distribution. Most Debian 12 OS CVEs are in this
#                      category and are excluded automatically — no entry here needed.
#   --severity HIGH,CRITICAL   Only fixable HIGH/CRITICAL issues block the pipeline.
#
# Entries in this file are for the narrow category of CVEs that:
#   a) Have a "fixed version" listed in Trivy (so --ignore-unfixed does NOT filter them), AND
#   b) Have been assessed as non-exploitable or non-applicable in this context.
#
# Policy: entries are added ONLY when ALL of the following are true:
#   1. Fixed Version appears in the Trivy report (--ignore-unfixed left it visible)
#   2. The vulnerability has been assessed for exploitability in this runtime context
#   3. A monitoring note is recorded so the entry is revisited when the fix is stable
#
# Every entry MUST include: CVE ID, date added, package, reason, and review trigger.
# Remove the entry immediately when the fixed version has been deployed.

# ─── NOTE ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# CVE-2026-0861 (libc6 / glibc memalign integer overflow) was previously listed
# here. It is now automatically suppressed by the --ignore-unfixed flag because
# Debian 12 (bookworm) has no patched libc6 build available. The entry has been
# removed to keep this file minimal. Monitor:
#   https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2026-0861
# Add an explicit entry here ONLY if a "fixed version" appears in Trivy's report
# and we still need to suppress it for a documented reason.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
